19/11/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US Senate on Friday (November 17th) unanimously endorsed a resolution calling for the timely admission into NATO of the so-called Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- as well as Georgia. 
The bill, sponsored by Indiana Senator Richard Lugar, stresses the reforms achieved by the Adriatic Charter states. 
It urges recognition of their progress at the upcoming NATO summit in Riga. 
(Vecernji list, A1 TV - 18/11/06; Hina, Telma TV, Makfax - 17/11/06)
